## Executive Overview

HFAT-X10 (Hyper-Flow Adaptive Transit) represents the next evolutionary stage beyond AFAT-X10 and AFAT-X10 V2.

While AFAT systems focused primarily on aerodynamic intelligence and airflow optimization, HFAT-X10 expands the concept of flow itself into a unified operational discipline.

Within HFAT-X10, flow is defined as:

* Airflow
* Thermal flow
* Hydraulic flow
* Energy flow
* Information flow
* Communications flow
* Mission-resource flow

The architecture establishes a common governance framework capable of coordinating all flow-dependent subsystems throughout the PI220 ecosystem.

HFAT-X10 serves as the first true multi-domain flow intelligence architecture.

