## 20. Strategic Assessment

HFAT-X10 represents the transition from subsystem optimization to ecosystem optimization.

Its significance lies in recognizing that aerospace performance is governed not by isolated components, but by the interaction of flows throughout the entire architecture.

By coordinating airflow, thermal flow, hydraulic flow, energy flow, information flow, and mission-resource flow, HFAT-X10 establishes the foundation for future autonomous aerospace ecosystems capable of self-optimization at scale.

